Hellboy
Ars Tribunus Militum
Registered: Dec 15, 1999Posts: 2934
Posted: Sat Jul 04, 2009 8:31 am
quote:I don't quite understand what the hell you'd want a bank in EVE for? Certain large projects like Capital Ship production require huge outlays of capital in order to acquire the blueprints and mineral resources required to begin production. That's without even thinking about running one or more POS, in order to have your own build slots for all those ship components.Many corporations do this kind of thing internally, where the trust relationships are stronger, in order to get the money together for big projects. This kind of public bank in EVE has always struck me as problematic because there's no deposit insurance. You are essentially just gambling your ISK, hoping that you make a decent return before getting ripped off.
